nv-detected agents to `but_agentlog::Agent` at [crates/but/src/lib.rs](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but/src/lib.rs:1432); `but-agentlog` only consumes the explicit enum. No weird duplication there.\\n\\n- Transcript parsing boundary is mostly right. Provider vocabulary stays in [transcript.rs](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/transcript.rs:46); GitMeta doesn’t parse Codex/Claude shapes directly.\\n\\n- Redaction split is acceptable. The redaction policy lives in [redaction.rs](/Users/kiril/src/gitbutler/crates/but-agentlog/src/redaction.rs:8); GitMeta applies it at the storage boundary, which is the right place.\"}}\n</subagent_notification>","tool_name":null,"tool_input":null,"source_record":{"timestamp":"2026-05-20T17:59:29.556Z","type":"response_item","payload":{"type":"message","role":"user"}}}